For pkgsrc imports:

1.  move/copy the package directory in the right place

2.  cd into it

3.  ../../wip/import-package.sh

4.  cd ..

5.  add it to $CATEGORY/Makefile
    pkglint -F in pkgsrc/$CATEGORY will help
    commit, message = category/Makefile: Add pkgname

Package adds, removals, moves, upgrades (other cases, see guide):

1.  make a changes entry
    
    Must have PKG_DEVELOPER=yes
	NetBSD: /etc/mk.conf
	Custom trees: sysprefix/etc/mk.conf    

    make help topic=cce
    
    cd category/pkg
    make cce CTYPE=Added NETBSD_LOGIN_NAME=bacon
    make cce CTYPE=Updated NETBSD_LOGIN_NAME=bacon
